Gura sama I'm worried you only make mason villagers, you could unlock the full potential of them so I made a list for you.

Armorer (Job site block: Blast Furnace)
- Apprentice (Chainmail Leggins, Chainmail Boots, Bell)
- Journeyman (Chainmail Helmet, Chainmail Chestplate, Shield)
- Expert (Enchanted Diamond Boots, Enchanted Diamond Helmet)
- Master (Enchanted Diamond Helmet, Enchanted Diamond Chesplate)
Butcher (Job site block: Smoker)
- Novice (Rabbit Stew)
- Apprentice (Cooked Porkchop, Cooked Chiken)
Cartographer (Job site block: Cartography Table)
- Novice (Empty Map)
- Apprentice (Ocean Explorer Map)
- Journeyman (Item Frame, Woodland Explorer Map)
Cleric (Job site block: Brewing Stand)

- Journeyman (Glowstone)
- Expert (Ender Pearl)
Farmer (Job site block: Composter)

- Journeyman (Cookie, Cake)
Fisherman (Job site block: Barrel)

Fletcher (Job site block: Fletching Table)

- Master (Enchanted Crossbow)
Leatherworker (Job site block: Cauldron)
- Novice (Leather Pants, Leather Tunic)

Librarian (Job site block: Lectern)

text:
I gotta say Minecraft water noises are weird.

You make a waterfall like Gura has here, and it's dead silent. But if you have a little uneven pool of water and it's super noisy on par with Watson Railway and Kiara's chicken shack.

Like shouldn't the water falling make noise? It makes plenty of noise when falling a short distance, but nothing for a big drop off of a cliff.

I guess it makes sense because otherwise pretty much all water would make noise, like how do distinguish between an ocean of water and a column of water. I mean all oceans are, is many columns of water right next to each other. But still it seems weird having a quiet waterfall.

text:
To be honest I doubt anyone in Hololive En really cares about the "don't talk about other streamers" rule. The rules are likely required to be there by Hololive regardless of if the streamers themselves actually care about those particular rules being followed or not.

Like really if you think about it, it is like... "Oh no, chat is talking about my friends/co-workers who I really love and care about! Whatever will I do? I hate my dear friends and co-workers! Chat stop talking about my friends who I have grown close with over the last year!"

It's just not realistic to think that they actually want you to follow that rule. It's quite obviously a requirement and not a choice to have that rule. You might make management upset at most but really none of the girls are going to care if you're talking about their friends and co-workers.
